Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.04,0:00:04.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We came to watch Hado Rokumichi's \Nconcert rehearsal...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.41,0:00:09.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,at which he was set to perform "ASACA," \Na song written seventeen years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.08,0:00:10.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.32,0:01:01.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even heaven is watching the \Nlabyrinths of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.41,0:01:03.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Full throttle reasoning skills \Npenetrate all mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.87,0:01:07.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In the shadow of the case happening on the \Nstage lurk Amuro, Okiya, and Vermouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.81,0:01:09.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.54,0:01:11.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.83,0:01:14.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.01,0:02:49.03,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(403,1)}The Traitor's Stage \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.69,0:02:46.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Traitor's Stage, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.33,0:02:54.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? The victim wrote the \Nnote on the paper himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.26,0:02:55.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.65,0:02:57.37,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to forensics,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.37,0:03:01.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,the paper came from the notebook \Nthe victim used to write lyrics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:06.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The handwriting matched the lyrics written \Non the other pages of the notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.24,0:03:10.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's likely the \Nvictim felt indebted to someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.35,0:03:13.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and that became their reason to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.95,0:03:15.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.82,0:03:18.80,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know about indebted, but he \Nmay have had an inferiority complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.17,0:03:24.76,Kanae,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Enjo Kanae (40) \NHado's Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.22,0:03:23.33,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hado often said he had \Nto work hard to keep up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.33,0:03:27.56,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}with other handsome musicians \Nsince he had an off-putting face.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.79,0:03:28.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.85,0:03:31.94,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,I told him not to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.44,0:03:36.44,Okuyasu,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Fuse Okuyasu (58) \NRecord Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.45,0:03:36.44,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I said the way he seemed difficult \Nto approach was part of his charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.74,0:03:40.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Hado-san \Nchanged his image recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.12,0:03:42.95,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he seemed softer than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.38,0:03:45.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Changed how?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.47,0:03:47.45,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Just his overall impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:49.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.06,0:03:53.38,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, there were \Nrumors Hado got plastic surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.38,0:03:58.08,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Although I think that was around the \Ntime he graduated from high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:59.30,Hirokazu,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Kajiya Hirokazu (51) \NMagazine Reporter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:04:00.71,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I told you before, that's all nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.42,0:04:03.71,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't have any money back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.71,0:04:07.70,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,We worked every day for \Na shipping company
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.70,0:04:10.85,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,to make enough money \Nfor him to be a musician.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.17,0:04:14.67,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,But Hado dumped you after \Nyou worked so hard together,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.67,0:04:17.73,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,and married another woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.73,0:04:20.36,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I think that was sixteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.60,0:04:24.63,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,And the song "ASACA" he was \Nset to announce at this concert
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.63,0:04:25.86,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,was composed seventeen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.23,0:04:29.71,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,There must be some reason he left it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.71,0:04:31.62,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,without lyrics for seventeen years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.93,0:04:34.33,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Right, pretty little manager?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.12,0:04:37.82,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.82,0:04:40.80,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,President, you must know something, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.35,0:04:45.71,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I heard Hado asked you \Nafter his previous concert,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.71,0:04:48.80,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,"Why didn't you say anything \Nfor seventeen years?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.14,0:04:51.29,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,And after your argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:54.81,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Hado suddenly announced he'd be \Nreleasing his new song "ASACA."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:04:57.81,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,There must be something going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.78,0:05:00.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.76,0:05:06.57,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Hado started working with my record \Ncompany seventeen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.12,0:05:10.28,DCMain,FYSE,0000,0000,0000,,I jokingly told him the real \Nreason I had him debut with us
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.28,0:05:14.88,DCMain,FYSE,0000,0000,0000,,was because I'd fallen in love with Enjo-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.88,0:05:17.21,DCMain,FYSE,0000,0000,0000,,and wanted to court her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.68,0:05:20.46,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd quit if that were true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.69,0:05:21.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.90,0:05:25.97,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't sound like a \Nmotive to murder Hado-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:29.02,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.02,0:05:30.22,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.55,0:05:34.60,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it impossible for anyone \Nto have committed this crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.76,0:05:38.60,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,You can't. It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.61,0:05:44.77,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Give up, Scotch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.70,0:06:04.96,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,His right hand was covered in blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.20,0:06:08.22,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,except for the tip of his thumb \Nand the back of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.71,0:06:12.72,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,That means he put his thumb on the trigger
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.42,0:06:15.21,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,and shot himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.02,0:06:20.17,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who gave him \Nyour gun and made him do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.04,0:06:25.59,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Akai Shuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.83,0:06:32.49,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,He would've had plenty of options \Nbesides killing himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.77,0:06:37.74,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.74,0:06:38.41,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.68,0:06:42.01,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,You've been glaring at him. What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.01,0:06:43.17,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:47.25,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I don't particularly care, but \Ncould you solve this soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.25,0:06:50.76,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous for me to stay \Nhere very long while in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.76,0:06:51.72,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.72,0:06:53.90,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.90,0:06:57.64,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get back to the office and \Nwrite an article about this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.82,0:07:01.30,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We need to check the \Ncontents of your bag first!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.30,0:07:02.65,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,You guys never give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.65,0:07:04.36,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you to let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.07,0:07:06.28,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.72,0:07:11.04,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:13.45,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:16.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.08,0:07:17.33,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.69,0:07:25.15,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hado-san's driver license.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.15,0:07:28.10,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He certainly seems unapproachable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.55,0:07:39.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,After viewing the images on the \Ncamera that was in your bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.45,0:07:42.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,it looks like you were secretly taking photos \Nof Hado-san as he entered the concert hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.62,0:07:45.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but he discovered you and tried \Nto take away your camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.63,0:07:48.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.47,0:07:49.23,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.64,0:07:51.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What did he say then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.79,0:07:53.99,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,He just said to stop taking pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.38,0:07:56.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Also, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.14,0:08:02.06,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,One of the band members scheduled \Nto perform with Hado-san
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:04.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,at tomorrow's concert was just \Narrested by narcotics agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.79,0:08:05.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.75,0:08:08.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,For possession of stimulants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:10.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.16,0:08:13.09,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.47,0:08:17.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find a... on the ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:21.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Azusa-neechan said she lost one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.50,0:08:22.96,DCItalic,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.90,0:08:25.10,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,...one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:36.37,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,No, we didn't find anything \Nlike that on the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.64,0:08:38.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then was anything missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.42,0:08:40.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Like wire or gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.94,0:08:45.34,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,The staff said both of those \Nwere missing from the tool box
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.34,0:08:47.60,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,at the edge of the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:52.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did the staff leave that folding \Nchair next to the tool box?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.25,0:08:56.39,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,No, they kept it farther offstage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.70,0:08:59.42,DCMain,STAFF A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, leave that stuff where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.42,0:09:01.39,DCMain,STAFF A,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the concert is canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.39,0:09:02.67,DCMain,STAFF B,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.67,0:09:04.77,DCMain,STAFF B,0000,0000,0000,,I just untied this, and \Nnow I have to retie it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.02,0:09:08.44,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you inspect the folding chair, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:10.50,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Not for prints yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.50,0:09:14.78,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,But he's taking it back along with \Nthe mic stand for further inspection.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.34,0:09:16.42,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.42,0:09:19.06,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you show me the bottom of the seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.06,0:09:19.53,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:21.28,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, just for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.28,0:09:22.54,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.52,0:09:27.54,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.81,0:09:29.54,DCItalic,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.27,0:09:34.95,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This got kind of crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.47,0:09:34.66,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Uh, are you done?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.95,0:09:36.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:38.04,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Coming through.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.70,0:09:40.66,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Out of the way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.42,0:09:43.89,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Out of the way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.24,0:09:45.19,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.60,0:09:46.85,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Move, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.21,0:09:49.15,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.15,0:09:54.23,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The suspicious woman who tried to \Nkidnap Conan-kun and Ai-chan said...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.01,0:09:58.51,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Move away from the brunette,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.51,0:10:00.68,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,if you don't want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.68,0:10:01.74,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:04.75,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Move it, Angel!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.57,0:10:07.61,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.47,0:10:13.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,By why would Azusa-san \Ncall me by the same name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.94,0:10:24.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You know how the killer \Nlifted the victim's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.82,0:10:26.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.04,0:10:27.35,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.82,0:10:33.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We passed the rope over the spotlight bar
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.88,0:10:37.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and tied the other end to Takagi-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.72,0:10:40.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but is one person really strong \Nenough to lift him out of the chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.82,0:10:42.32,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:46.24,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,First you create a loop with the rope hanging
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:48.82,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,from the bar while standing \Nnext to the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.82,0:10:53.04,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Wrap the bottom loop around \Nthe top loop two times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.54,0:10:56.30,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,While twisting the lower loop,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.78,0:11:01.05,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,pass the section hanging \Ndown through the loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.52,0:11:06.72,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Hook the resulting large loop \Nonto the armrest of the seat
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.24,0:11:08.73,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,about two meters below, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.08,0:11:11.23,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Next, pass the end of the rope
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.65,0:11:14.43,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,without the loops under the armrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.43,0:11:16.68,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Create the same loops as before \Nand pass the rope through.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.68,0:11:20.70,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Now hook the large loop and rope
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.70,0:11:22.57,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,on the armrest of a chair \Nabout four meters away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:26.08,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Create a third loop and \Npass the rope through,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.40,0:11:31.08,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,and this time, hook the \Nlarge loop onto a chair
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.45,0:11:32.96,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,about eight meters away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.43,0:11:37.09,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Now all you have to do is return \Nto the third set of small loops
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.48,0:11:41.58,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,you created and pull on the leftover rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.66,0:11:44.93,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-san, you seem like \Nthe weakest person here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.93,0:11:46.37,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you pull on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.37,0:11:48.19,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.83,0:11:51.32,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:56.21,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt I'll be able to lift him, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.13,0:12:01.95,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.35,0:12:04.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:07.24,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,It's the principle of pulleys, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.24,0:12:08.08,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.52,0:12:12.98,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,The small loops created along \Nthe rope function as pulleys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.26,0:12:18.84,Force,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(710,1)}Force
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.26,0:12:18.84,Force2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(710,1)}Force
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.98,0:12:16.84,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Each set of loops doubles, \Nquadruples, and octuples
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.84,0:12:18.84,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,the strength at which the rope pulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.10,0:12:22.09,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're using rope rather than pulleys,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:24.75,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,the strength isn't actually \Noctupled due to friction,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:27.10,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,but if you use a light \Nand slippery enough rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:29.89,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,even Sonoko-san can lift Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.42,0:12:33.66,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the culprit used \Nnot the strength of several people,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.66,0:12:36.77,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,but lifted Hado-san alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.12,0:12:39.77,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, this is \Nknown as a shipping knot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.77,0:12:44.03,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Shipping workers use this \Nknot to secure cargo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.50,0:12:49.44,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the most likely suspect \Nwho lifted Hado-san's body
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.79,0:12:52.91,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,is his manager who worked \Nfor a shipping company
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.33,0:12:54.95,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,when she was younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.95,0:12:55.54,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.64,0:13:00.56,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Enjo Kanae-san, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:05.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I can see how she lifted him, but how \Ndid she tie the rope to the seats?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.78,0:13:07.34,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,That's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.51,0:13:10.47,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,First, after lifting the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.98,0:13:13.98,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,she temporarily secured the \Nrope by tying it to a nearby seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.59,0:13:19.36,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Then she wrapped a wire around the \Nrope leading upwards around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.94,0:13:23.75,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Once the rope coming from the \Nceiling is secured using the wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:27.35,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,the remaining rope can be untied \Nand reattached to the seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.35,0:13:28.87,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,and the wire can be removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.27,0:13:33.52,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,The best part of the shipping knot \Nis that it can be untied easily
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.52,0:13:36.78,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,since it doesn't actually create any knots, \Nbut if it's done using a brand new rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.78,0:13:39.69,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,then it leaves behind telltale marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.69,0:13:43.14,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why after retying \Nthe rope to the seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.14,0:13:46.53,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,you cut the end using the \Nbox cutter in the tool box,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.53,0:13:51.89,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,and left it coiled next to the tool \Nbox at the edge of the stage, right,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.59,0:13:53.64,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Enjo-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.46,0:13:58.27,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,You can't assume she did it just because
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.43,0:14:01.09,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,she used to work for a shipping company.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:03.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the size of her feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:04.90,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,H-Her feet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.15,0:14:11.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shipping workers coil rope \Nby wrapping it like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.40,0:14:14.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The inner loop is approximately
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.59,0:14:17.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the size of the person's foot,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.94,0:14:21.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,since the space between the elbow and the \Nwrist is about the size of their foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.45,0:14:27.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since the rope found at the crime scene was \Nin loops about the size of Ran-neechan's feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.84,0:14:32.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we thought the rope might have been \Ncoiled by the smaller manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.25,0:14:34.80,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.80,0:14:37.90,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,So after seventeen years,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.90,0:14:41.69,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,the manager's feelings for \NHado turned into hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:44.15,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you shouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.15,0:14:46.15,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,We're still not sure that she did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.66,0:14:48.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Contact lenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.47,0:14:52.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,As his manager, you must've noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.01,0:14:55.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hado-san was wearing contact lenses \Nto make his irises look larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.98,0:14:57.27,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.27,0:14:59.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed after looking at \NHado-san's driver license
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.52,0:15:04.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and comparing it to the images \Nthe magazine reporter took today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.97,0:15:10.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,One of the lenses is stuck to your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.81,0:15:11.52,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.94,0:15:17.39,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.66,0:15:19.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.49,0:15:20.34,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.16,0:15:22.74,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.74,0:15:25.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,While you were lifting his body,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.48,0:15:28.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,one of them fell onto your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.39,0:15:30.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough evidence for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.39,0:15:31.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell us the rest at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.69,0:15:34.03,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute. Did you really do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.42,0:15:38.88,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,After supporting him for seventeen \Nyears, why did you have to kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.88,0:15:39.91,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.06,0:15:44.02,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,She can't answer that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.45,0:15:48.37,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, she didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.10,0:15:50.16,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.16,0:15:52.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.05,0:15:56.47,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you think we found \Nthe other circle lens?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:16:01.42,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,It was under the folding chair \Nleft at the edge of the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.42,0:16:05.98,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, that chair had fallen \Nunder his feet after he was hanging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.70,0:16:11.52,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,There's also the baseball \Ntied to the kite string.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.52,0:16:15.81,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,It was used to pass the rope over the \Nbar by tying the other end to the rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.81,0:16:19.19,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,throwing the ball so that \Nthe kite string would pass
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.19,0:16:23.37,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,over the bar on the ceiling, \Nand pulling on the string.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:25.22,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean to be rude,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.22,0:16:29.68,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,but I doubt Enjo-san would have been able to \Nthrow the ball high enough to clear the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.13,0:16:33.90,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Although Hado-san, known for his strong arm on \Nhis high school baseball team, is another story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.38,0:16:41.39,DCNote,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,682)}I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:39.11,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's the note found \Nin Hado-san's breast pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.90,0:16:41.73,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You know where this is going, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.73,0:16:43.56,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He killed himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.96,0:16:44.72,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.06,0:16:47.20,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,He hung himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.20,0:16:51.32,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,and she disguised it to look \Nlike a murder after finding him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.61,0:16:53.92,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you try to hide his suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.92,0:16:56.95,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Something must've happened seventeen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.25,0:17:00.98,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Were you worried about what \Nwe discussed the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.56,0:17:03.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.04,0:17:05.55,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Seventeen years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.55,0:17:07.81,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,she was pregnant with Hado's child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.81,0:17:08.71,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,Fuse-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:11.82,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Saying it was for their unborn child,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.21,0:17:16.53,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,the freshly debuted Hado locked himself \Nin his studio and wrote music.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.94,0:17:20.00,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,He stayed up so many nights \Nin a row, I thought he'd die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.48,0:17:23.63,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,When she came to stop him, she \Ncollapsed in front of the studio
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.63,0:17:25.48,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,and miscarried.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.06,0:17:31.98,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,At the hospital, she asked \Nme not to tell Hado about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.40,0:17:33.54,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.54,0:17:38.05,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Since "ASACA" was the song he \Nwrote for that unborn child,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.05,0:17:41.62,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,he held onto it for seventeen years, \Nunable to write the lyrics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.25,0:17:44.96,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,When he learned what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:48.24,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,he felt responsible and attempted to write \Nlyrics for the child and release the song.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.24,0:17:50.70,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,But unable to write,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.70,0:17:55.28,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,he left the message "sorry" \Nand chose to die instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.28,0:17:58.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But why was it necessary to \Nmake it look like murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.71,0:18:03.22,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want his family \Nto know he killed himself
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.64,0:18:06.98,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,over his ex's baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.17,0:18:11.64,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,So I took his phone with the \Nmessage "goodbye" in his outbox
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.64,0:18:14.86,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,out of his pocket
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.25,0:18:18.46,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,and raised him up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.50,0:18:27.11,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,What an idiot to make a woman \Ncry even after his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:31.38,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't put this in your article!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.99,0:18:34.59,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I followed Hado for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.00,0:18:38.80,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I crawled along the ground day \Nafter day looking for a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.80,0:18:42.85,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,And now the story I've found is also \Nthe biggest scandal in Hado's career.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.10,0:18:45.90,DCMain,ENJO,0000,0000,0000,,Please. Please don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.90,0:18:49.10,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I like to think I understood \NHado better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.84,0:18:52.11,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you didn't ask me not \Nto, I wouldn't write about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.01,0:18:57.54,DCMain,KAJIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Such an overly sentimental story \Ndoesn't suit a rock and roller.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:02.62,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,We still don't know why the "CA" in "ASACA"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.03,0:19:05.92,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,was spelled the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.92,0:19:08.62,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I asked Hado about it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.30,0:19:12.75,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,Since he heard about the pregnancy at \Na morning café after an all-nighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.75,0:19:14.62,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,if it was a girl, he wanted \Nto call her "Asaca,"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.62,0:19:18.88,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,taking the "ca" from "café."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.36,0:19:21.46,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Sounds good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.46,0:19:25.52,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But if you were good enough friends \Nfor him to tell you that story,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.52,0:19:28.89,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,why did you turn on him and \Npush him towards retirement?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.22,0:19:30.27,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know about his
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.27,0:19:34.61,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,band member who was just \Narrested for possession?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.90,0:19:38.07,DCMain,FUSE,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't know anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.91,0:19:41.57,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,You already heard about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.78,0:19:45.58,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,The story's already online.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.93,0:19:47.39,DCItalic,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.88,0:19:50.83,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed, Scotch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.16,0:19:55.34,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,You took my gun while pretending \Nto be thrown by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.66,0:19:58.08,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I won't beg for my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.08,0:20:01.34,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,but before you shoot me, don't you \Nwant to hear what I have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.71,0:20:05.18,DCItalic,SCOTCH,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't draw your gun to shoot you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.68,0:20:06.68,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.02,0:20:13.85,DCItalic,SCOTCH,0000,0000,0000,,I drew it to do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.46,0:20:16.44,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.41,0:20:23.15,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not possible to pull \Nthe trigger of a revolver
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.61,0:20:26.95,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,when someone's holding the cylinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.62,0:20:29.72,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't kill yourself, Scotch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.32,0:20:32.93,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,You're not meant to die here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.93,0:20:33.58,DCItalic,SCOTCH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.09,0:20:38.02,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Akai Shuichi, an agent of the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.02,0:20:41.84,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Like you, I'm a dog trying \Nto sink my teeth into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:46.53,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Now let go of the gun and listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.07,0:20:50.69,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Helping you escape will be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.23,0:20:52.36,DCItalic,SCOTCH,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.76,0:21:06.82,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.30,0:21:10.62,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,He took my gun so he could destroy this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.47,0:21:16.27,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,This cellphone that likely contained \Ndata on his family and friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.96,0:21:25.76,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Traitors will be punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.87,0:21:28.26,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.13,0:21:35.77,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I have a strong urge to \Nfold down your turtleneck,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.07,0:21:38.98,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,but I'll restrain myself for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.50,0:21:41.40,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,See you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.22,0:21:45.11,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.55,0:23:13.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, Azusa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.13,0:23:15.16,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.69,0:23:19.50,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're not Azusa-san, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.53,0:23:21.75,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're that woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.49,0:23:25.72,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,who called me Angel before, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.72,0:23:27.26,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, Ran-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.60,0:23:30.76,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come any closer to our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.08,0:23:35.64,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you're my treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.24,0:23:38.45,DCItalic,VEMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.87,0:23:44.40,DCItalic,VEMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,one of only two in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.25,0:23:47.22,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.22,0:23:49.28,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's so awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.68,0:23:52.06,DCMain,ICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I supposed to put these books?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.06,0:23:55.53,DCMain,ICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,The store's already packed \Nwith books we can't sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.15,0:23:59.08,DCMain,YUJIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Finding a used book is a once \Nin a lifetime experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.08,0:24:03.50,DCMain,YUJIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Someday these will pass into the \Nhands of the people looking for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.80,0:24:05.39,DCMain,ICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Whistling Bookstore
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.69,0:24:13.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Whistling Bookstore!"
